# Copy to `.env.local` for local overrides (not committed).

# Google Maps (browser key; optional)
# VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=

# API origin for Capacitor / native builds only — scheme + host, no trailing slash.
# Example: https://mainspring.au
# Leave unset for normal web dev (Vite proxies /v1 to the backend) and production Docker (same host as API).
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=

# ── Capacitor (store apps) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# After changing web code:  npm run build && npm run cap:sync
# Open native IDEs:        npm run cap:open:android   |   npm run cap:open:ios
# iOS: run pod install inside ios/App on macOS once CocoaPods is installed.

# Native (Capacitor): JWTs persist in Keychain/Keystore (@aparajita/capacitor-secure-storage);
# remember-me flag uses @capacitor/preferences. Resume triggers proactive refresh (NativeChrome).
# Status bar, splash, and Android hardware back: main.tsx + NativeChrome.tsx.

# Google Maps (build-time): for store WebViews, allow HTTP referrers https://localhost/* and
# capacitor://localhost/* on the same browser key, or maps/geocode will fail in the app.
# VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=
